[x] Delete the dead Turtle serializer $graphd/src/graph/serialize.rs (serialize_acts/_closed/_open_to_turtle, dump_store_to_turtle) is pub-use'd but called by nothing; no Turtle subcommand in main.rs and archival went plaintext. Remove the module and its exports (~105 LOC).$ !1 %2026-07-18T13:05 #019f76ca-c04b-7341-ad01-e0c08f8ad41b
[x] Hoist NdjsonEmitter into core $The concrete rotating-file NdjsonEmitter is copy-pasted in cli and lsp; both already implement core's TelemetryEmitter trait over core's TelemetryEvent enum. Move the writer to core (generic, no runtime-specific types) and delete both copies. Do NOT add lsp/cli-specific events to core.$ !1 %2026-07-18T15:11 #019f76ca-f3a6-7fb2-a96d-0e37230f37e9
[x] Move config loading into core as shared substrate $Move config loading from the CLI environment_reader into core so CLI, LSP, and graphd share one source-and-precedence stack (defaults, global, project, project.local, env). Core owns file discovery and precedence and path resolution; each tool deserializes its own struct and extends with tool-specific fields (CLI keeps cli_format and cli_indent). Prerequisite for graphd standing alone.$ !1 %2026-07-18T17:27 #019f77b2-d6b2-7ea2-96ed-06e8e5f50429
[x] graphd becomes a standalone tool $Make graphd usable directly by humans and agents, not just the CLI. It self-discovers config via core instead of receiving it in the request envelope, and owns a named-query registry where each entry carries a name, its sparql, and a declared shape (list, tree, or graph). It owns output modes (rows, ndjson, nested json, jsonld) behind a clean argument interface. The CLI consumes this same public interface, not a private protocol. Someone can install graphd without the CLI. Drop the config field from the stdin request once self-discovery lands.$ !2 %2026-07-18T19:30 #019f76cb-c2f7-7741-9153-1312f4d15d33
[x] Rescope query output spec to graphd semantic contract $Query output specification was written when the graph lived in core, so it claimed one payload for every consumer. Rescope it: the spec governs graphd semantic jsonld output and the federation contract where meaning travels with the data. Document the CLI presentation contract separately, including the shape taxonomy (list to ndjson, tree to nested json, graph to triples) and the terminal versus pipe axis. The meaning-travels principle still holds for the semantic layer.$ !3 %2026-07-18T21:48 #019f77b2-d6d0-7193-acb8-3c54563cf27c
[x] move clearhead.nvim query reads directly to graphd $Add explicit graphd binary discovery/configuration to clearhead.nvim and invoke graphd's public index interface directly. Keep clearhead only for mutation verbs and clearhead-lsp for document intelligence. Prove the existing read -> act-by-id -> re-read living loop with all three binaries independently addressable.$ %2026-07-22T13:39 #019f8b8a-723c-7350-b4a7-ef84bf6cb02c
[x] retire the CLI query forwarding facade $After editor and documented consumers call graphd directly, remove clearhead query subcommands, graph_backend query forwarding, duplicated query format arguments, and facade tests/docs. Preserve only core-backed mutation/workspace commands in clearhead; graphd remains independently installable and owns query stdout, stderr, formats, and exit semantics.$ %2026-07-22T13:44 <019f8b8a-723c-7350-b4a7-ef84bf6cb02c #019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce
[x] implement the tree query family with work-map $Add queries/tree discovery and execution around complete standard SELECT files. Use work-map.sparql as the proving query over charter, subcharter, action, and child-action hierarchy; validate canonical id plus parent semantics, emit nested JSON for machines and an indented terminal tree, and run the same .sparql unchanged in an external SPARQL tool.$ %2026-07-22T13:49 <019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce #019f8b8a-b7ef-7731-b870-8719fd562c33
[x] implement the graph query family with dependencies $Add queries/graph discovery and standard CONSTRUCT execution. Use dependencies.sparql as the proving query over action identity, labels, states, charter membership, and predecessor edges; emit JSON-LD plus an explicit standard RDF format and a terminal summary, and prove the .sparql/result round-trip through external RDF tooling.$ %2026-07-22T13:53 <019f8b8a-840e-78b0-af82-938b90d7a9ce #019f8b8a-b7fc-7e03-a507-2e47b88f4740
[x] graphd owns portable query families and output formats $Establish graphd as the direct public read/query/export tool. Standard .sparql files opt into index, tree, or graph consumer contracts by family directory; graphd validates and serializes them, while raw/named SPARQL stays unrestricted. The clearhead CLI remains a mutation and workspace-lifecycle convenience and should not forward, decode, or implement graph queries. Neovim and other clients call graphd directly for reads and clearhead for identity-addressed writes. Index output is proven; complete the direct-client cutover before implementing tree/work-map and graph/dependencies showcases.$ !2 %2026-07-22T13:53 #019f76ca-f3b1-7613-a0de-74f453f8576c
